<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.1.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2020-11-10T11:08:56+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Hermosawave Photography</title><subtitle>A series of daily landscape photographs by Daniel Sofer, over 16 years running.</subtitle><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><entry><title type="html">Still Leaves・落ち葉</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201109/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Still Leaves・落ち葉" /><published>2020-11-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/still-leaves</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201109/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Leaves in the morning sunlight, after a rain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    雨上がりの朝日に照らされる葉っぱ。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html">Leaves in the morning sunlight, after a rain.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00584.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Colors on the Oi River・大堰川の紅葉</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201108/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Colors on the Oi River・大堰川の紅葉" /><published>2020-11-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/oi-river</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201108/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Peaceful Arashiyama in the morning. I wonder if this view is much different than it was 1000 years ago...
&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emperor_Saga&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Emperor Saga&lt;/a&gt; lived in this area during the 9th century, so I’m sure people came to enjoy the view even then.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    朝の静かな嵐山。 この眺めは1000年前とは違うのでしょうか？
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%B5%AF%E5%B3%A8%E5%A4%A9%E7%9A%87&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;嵯峨天皇&lt;/a&gt;は9世紀にこの地域に住んでいたので、その頃にもこの景色を楽しむ人が出てきたのでしょう。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html">Peaceful Arashiyama in the morning. I wonder if this view is much different than it was 1000 years ago... Emperor Saga lived in this area during the 9th century, so I’m sure people came to enjoy the view even then.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00522.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Tenju-an Garden・天授庵の庭園</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201107/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tenju-an Garden・天授庵の庭園" /><published>2020-11-07T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-07T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tenju-an</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201107/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    The east garden of Tenju-an, one of the subtemples around Nanzen-ji, created in the 14th century.
&lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    南禅寺の天授庵の東庭は、14世紀に造られました。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Gardens" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html">The east garden of Tenju-an, one of the subtemples around Nanzen-ji, created in the 14th century.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00451.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Murin-an・無鄰菴</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201106/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Murin-an・無鄰菴" /><published>2020-11-06T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-06T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/murin-an</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201106/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Autumn colors reflecting in the pond at Murin-an villa.
&lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    無鄰菴の池に映る秋の色。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html">Autumn colors reflecting in the pond at Murin-an villa.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00411.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Maple Leaves・もみじ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201104/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Maple Leaves・もみじ" /><published>2020-11-04T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-04T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/red-maple</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201104/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Colors are changing, but it remains only an occasional orange tree in a sea of green. Taken at Nison-in Temple.
&lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    色は少しずつ変わりつつあり、今まで緑一色だったところにオレンジ色の木が少し見えてきました。 二尊院で撮影。   
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html">Colors are changing, but it remains only an occasional orange tree in a sea of green. Taken at Nison-in Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00348.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Nijo Castle・二条城</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201103/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Nijo Castle・二条城" /><published>2020-11-03T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-03T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/nijo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201103/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    The ornate Ninomaru Gate at Nijo Castle. 
&lt;/p&gt; 

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    二条城の絢爛な二の丸門。    
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Castles" /><summary type="html">The ornate Ninomaru Gate at Nijo Castle.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2020/2011_A7R00331.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Sogenchi Garden・曹源池庭園</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201102/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sogenchi Garden・曹源池庭園" /><published>2020-11-02T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2020-11-02T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/sogenchi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/201102/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
